A function in JavaScript is of reference type.
(function () {}) === (function () {}) //=&gt; false  Ouroborian array: An array that contains itself.
var ouroboros=[]; ouroboros[0]=ouroboros; //=&gt; [ [Circular] ]  void is an operator that takes any value and evaluates to undefined, always. If you want to return undefined you may use:
return void 0; //=&gt;undefined  Any value after void will work, but by convention you better use void 0;
